rest_of_day_open: The remainder of the week seems like it will be another bland routine--the wife will be going into work while I work from home and take care of things around the house. A friend may visit but not until the weekend, and if he does so it will only be a brief stop with nothing truly planned.  --so, again, rather bland and usual.
critical_positive: The only factor that seemed to carry the conversation was our similarities about online work. Our thought processes on how the pandemic has effected the country and how we plan our income were another common thread. Being able to stretch these thoughts and feelings out was the saving grace of the conversation.
critical_negative: I felt that even though the similarities on the topics were there, it felt rather singular--as in basically only one thought the entire conversation. Any other topic was basically overshadowed and felt one-sided. When this wasn't being discussed the conversation seemed to be full-stop and everything would round back to the initial subject.

rest_of_day_open: I will be working more hours because we will be shifting to holiday hours soon. I see it going somewhere in the middle to halfway decent. I will try to keep good quality home time in the balance of work and non work. That is always important to me for good times.
critical_positive: Most of the conversation was one-sided for making nice money with surveys and studies. I always talked about I do not want a second job where I have to go and work for someone else. It is always enjoyable to make money at home where we can be in charged of when we work.
critical_negative: We talked too much about doing surveys....we did not even exchanged names...most of these conversations are really good but there is always points where each party looks at their watches. Still our conversation over all was very good because we enjoyed the fact the each of us showed up for the talk.
